    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The community drains into the Rockaway River, which flows east to the Passaic River at the Essex County border.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lower_Berkshire_Valley%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Roxbury Township, where the CDP is located, was founded in 1740 and grew around iron mining, forges that supplied George Washington, and the 1827 Morris Canal.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6,
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://attend.roxburylibrary.org/historic-walking-tour-16894"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The historic Roxbury Walking Tour covers 23 stops on Main Street, including the Silas Riggs Saltbox House dating back to the Revolutionary War.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://attend.roxburylibrary.org/historic-walking-tour-16894"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The Roxbury Historical Society operates the Silas Riggs Saltbox House and publishes books on township history.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://attend.roxburylibrary.org/historic-walking-tour-16894"
    },
